Yes, you can log the header structure while masking the actual API key. For example, in Node.js you might log a version of the header like:

console.log({ 'Authorization': 'Bearer ' + process.env.API_KEY.slice(0, 4) + '****' });

This way, you verify that the header is correctly formatted without exposing the full key. Let me know if this helps or if you encounter any further issues.
